        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">On average between 20214 and 2018, in France + Belgium + Netherlands  73 000 tons of fibre, short, scutched were produced per year. Source : statistic data for production of retted straw and of long and short fibres. The data was gathered by the Flax-Linen Economic Observatory of the Alliance for Linen-Flax and Hemp, from national organisations for flax cultivation and scutching in France, Belgium and the Netherlands. Assumed 30% of the global production volume is used for fibre, silk. Expert judgement.</productionVolumeComment>
